Introduction

This report documents the steps taken to preprocess and analyze the SOEP data for health-related outcomes: subjective and objective health measures, predictors, and control variables. The transformations include cleaning, imputing missing values, and deriving new variables.

1. Setup

## There are a lot of missing in years 2011, 2012 and 2013. Not to lose too many information, we will impute these values within each person with the mean of 2010 and 2014, other missings will be dropped.
main <- main %>%
  rename(worr_health_categorical = plh0035) %>%
  mutate(
    worr_health_categorical = case_when(
      worr_health_categorical < 0 ~ NA_real_,
      TRUE ~ worr_health_categorical
    )
  ) %>%
  group_by(pid) %>%
  mutate(
    worr_health_categorical = if_else(
      syear %in% c(2011, 2012, 2013) & is.na(worr_health_categorical),
      floor(
        mean(
          worr_health_categorical[syear %in% c(2010, 2014)],
          na.rm = TRUE
        )
      ),
      worr_health_categorical
    )
  ) %>%
  ungroup() %>%
  drop_na(worr_health_categorical) %>%
  mutate(
    worr_health_categorical = factor(
      worr_health_categorical, levels = c(3, 2, 1),
      labels = c("no worries", "worries a little", "worries a lot")
    ),
    worr_health_dummy = if_else(
      worr_health_categorical %in% c("worries a lot", "worries a little"), 1, 0
    )
  ) %>%
  # Drop any rows with NA in worr_health_categorical
  drop_na(worr_health_categorical)
# Visualisation: Bar plot (categorical)
ggplot(main, aes(x = worr_health_categorical)) +
  geom_bar(fill = "coral") +
  labs(
    title = "Distribution of Worries About Health",
    x = "Worries About Health",
    y = "Count"
  ) +
  theme_minimal()

# Calculate past health and health differences
main <- main %>%

# Create health decline dummy for 2 years into the future
main <- main %>%
  arrange(pid, syear) %>%

      !is.na(health_in_2yrs) & health_in_2yrs >= health ~ 0,
      TRUE ~ NA_real_

  ungroup()

3.2 Hospital Stay

# Create `hospital_stay` variable
main <- main %>%
  mutate(
    # Handle ple0055 transformations
    ple0055 = case_when(
      ple0055 %in% c(-1, -3) ~ NA_real_,  # Drop rows where values indicate refusal (-1, -3)
      ple0055 %in% c(-8, -5) & 
        !is.na(lag(ple0055, order_by = syear)) & 
        !is.na(lead(ple0055, order_by = syear)) ~ 
        (lag(ple0055, order_by = syear) + lead(ple0055, order_by = syear)) / 2,  # Impute missing values
      ple0055 >= 0 ~ ple0055,  # Keep valid non-negative values
      TRUE ~ NA_real_  # Set all other cases to NA
    ),
    # Handle ple0056 transformations
    ple0056 = case_when(
      ple0056 %in% c(-1, -3) ~ NA_real_,  # Drop rows where values indicate refusal (-1, -3)
      ple0056 %in% c(-8, -5) & 
        !is.na(lag(ple0056, order_by = syear)) & 
        !is.na(lead(ple0056, order_by = syear)) ~ 
        (lag(ple0056, order_by = syear) + lead(ple0056, order_by = syear)) / 2,  # Impute missing values
      ple0056 >= 0 ~ ple0056,  # Keep valid non-negative values
      TRUE ~ NA_real_  # Set all other cases to NA
    )
  ) %>%
  # Drop rows where either ple0055 or ple0056 is NA
  filter(!is.na(ple0055) & !is.na(ple0056)) %>%
  # Ensure both ple0055 and ple0056 are non-negative before calculation
  mutate(
    ple0055 = if_else(ple0055 < 0, NA_real_, ple0055),
    ple0056 = if_else(ple0056 < 0, NA_real_, ple0056),
    hospital_stay = ple0055 + ple0056  # Calculate hospital stay
  ) %>%
  # Drop rows with negative hospital_stay
  filter(hospital_stay >= 0) %>%
  # Drop original columns
  select(-ple0055, -ple0056)
#Visualisation: Histogram
ggplot(main, aes(x = hospital_stay)) +
  geom_histogram(binwidth = 1, fill = "skyblue", color = "black", alpha = 0.7) +
  labs(
    title = "Distribution of Hospital Stays",
    x = "Number of Days in Hospital",
    y = "Count"
  ) +
  theme_minimal()

3.3 Impairement Variables

# Create impaired_stairs and impaired_tiring_tasks
main <- main %>%
  group_by(pid) %>%
  mutate(
    # Handle ple0004 transformations
    ple0004 = ifelse(ple0004 < -2, NA_real_, ple0004),
    ple0004 = if_else(
      syear %in% 1999:2001 & is.na(ple0004),
      ple0004[syear == 2002][1],  # Use the 2002 value if it exists
      ple0004
     ),
    ple0004 = ifelse(
      ple0004 %in% c(-5, -8) & !is.na(lag(ple0004, order_by = syear)) & !is.na(lead(ple0004, order_by = syear)),
      (lag(ple0004, order_by = syear) + lead(ple0004, order_by = syear)) / 2, ple0004
    ),
    ple0004 = ifelse(is.na(ple0004), 3, ple0004),  # Default unresolved NA to 3 ("no impairment")
    
    # Handle ple0005 transformations
    ple0005 = ifelse(ple0005 < -2, NA_real_, ple0005),
    ple0005 = ifelse(
      ple0005 == -1 & !is.na(lag(ple0005, order_by = syear)) & !is.na(lead(ple0005, order_by = syear)),
      (lag(ple0005, order_by = syear) + lead(ple0005, order_by = syear)) / 2, ple0005
    ),
    ple0005 = ifelse(is.na(ple0005), 3, ple0005)  # Default unresolved NA to 3 ("no impairment")
  ) %>%
  ungroup() %>% 
  mutate(
    # Calculate impaired_stairs
    impaired_stairs = case_when(
      ple0004 %in% c(1, 2) ~ 1,  # Impaired
      ple0004 == 3 ~ 0        # Not impaired
    ),
    
    # Calculate impaired_tiring_tasks
    impaired_tiring_tasks = case_when(
      ple0005 %in% c(1, 2) ~ 1,  # Impaired
      ple0005 == 3 ~ 0         # Not impaired
    )
  ) %>%
  # Drop rows where BOTH ple0004 and ple0005 are NA
  filter(!is.na(impaired_tiring_tasks) & !is.na(impaired_stairs))

#Visusalition: Bar plots- stairs
ggplot(main, aes(x = factor(impaired_stairs))) +
  geom_bar(fill = "skyblue", color = "black") +
  labs(
    title = "Distribution of Impaired Stairs",
    x = "Impairment in Climbing Stairs (1 = Impaired, 0 = Not Impaired)",
    y = "Count"
  ) +
  theme_minimal()

3.4. Illnesses: Special Potential Specification

# Create illnesses variable
illness_vars <- c("ple0011", "ple0012", "ple0013", "ple0014", "ple0015", 
                  "ple0016", "ple0017", "ple0018", "ple0019", "ple0020", 
                  "ple0021", "ple0022", "ple0023")

main <- main %>%
  arrange(pid, syear) %>%  # Ensure data is ordered by pid and syear
  group_by(pid) %>%
  mutate(across(
    all_of(illness_vars),
    ~ case_when(
      . %in% c(-8, -5) ~ {  # Impute -8 and -5 using the closest year's value
        temp <- .
        for (i in seq_along(temp)) {
          if (temp[i] %in% c(-8, -5)) {
            lag_val <- lag(temp, default = NA_real_, order_by = syear)[i]
            lead_val <- lead(temp, default = NA_real_, order_by = syear)[i]
            temp[i] <- if (!is.na(lag_val)) lag_val else lead_val
          }
        }
        temp
      },
      . == -2 ~ 0,  # Transform -2 into 0
      TRUE ~ .  # Keep all other valid values
    )
  )) %>%
  ungroup() %>%
  arrange(pid, syear) %>%
  group_by(pid) %>%
  mutate(across(
    all_of(illness_vars),
    ~ if_else(is.na(.), lag(., order_by = syear), .)
  )) %>%
  mutate(across(
    all_of(illness_vars),
    ~ if_else(is.na(.), lead(., order_by = syear), .)
  )) %>%
  ungroup() %>%
  mutate(across(
    all_of(illness_vars),
    ~ if_else(. < 0, NA_real_, .)  # Replace remaining negative values with NA
  )) %>%
  mutate(
    illnesses = rowSums(across(all_of(illness_vars)), na.rm = TRUE)  # Calculate the sum of illnesses
  )
# Ensure illnesses is rounded to integers
main <- main %>%
  mutate(illnesses = round(illnesses))

# Visualisation: Histogram with integer bins
ggplot(main, aes(x = illnesses)) +
  geom_histogram(binwidth = 1, fill = "skyblue", color = "black", alpha = 0.7, center = 0.5) +
  scale_x_continuous(breaks = seq(0, max(main$illnesses, na.rm = TRUE), by = 1)) +
  labs(
    title = "Distribution of Illness Counts",
    x = "Number of Illnesses",
    y = "Count"
  ) +
  theme_minimal()

# Create life_satisfaction and health_satisfaction variables
main <- main %>%
  arrange(pid, syear) %>%  # Ensure data is ordered by pid and syear
  group_by(pid) %>%
  mutate(
    # Impute for plh0182
    plh0182 = ifelse(plh0182 %in% c(-5, -8), NA_real_, plh0182),  # Replace -5 and -8 with NA
    plh0182 = {
      temp <- plh0182
      for (i in seq_len(n())) {
        # Check for missing values and use nearest available value from lag or lead
        if (is.na(temp[i])) {
          lag_val <- lag(temp, default = NA_real_, order_by = syear)[i]
          lead_val <- lead(temp, default = NA_real_, order_by = syear)[i]
          temp[i] <- if (!is.na(lag_val)) lag_val else lead_val
        }
      }
      temp
    },
    # Impute for plh0171
    plh0171 = ifelse(plh0171 %in% c(-5, -8), NA_real_, plh0171),  # Replace -5 and -8 with NA
    plh0171 = {
      temp <- plh0171
      for (i in seq_len(n())) {
        # Check for missing values and use nearest available value from lag or lead
        if (is.na(temp[i])) {
          lag_val <- lag(temp, default = NA_real_, order_by = syear)[i]
          lead_val <- lead(temp, default = NA_real_, order_by = syear)[i]
          temp[i] <- if (!is.na(lag_val)) lag_val else lead_val
        }
      }
      temp
    }
  ) %>%
  ungroup() %>%
  filter(plh0182 >= 0 & plh0182 <= 10) %>%  # Filter valid range for life satisfaction
  mutate(
    life_satisfaction = plh0182
  ) %>%
  filter(plh0171 >= 0 & plh0171 <= 10) %>%  # Filter valid range for health satisfaction

3.2.2 BMI

# Process height and weight
main <- main %>%
  mutate(
    # Rename and handle outliers
    height = case_when(
      ple0006 > 245 ~ NA_real_,  # Outliers above 245 cm are set to NA
      ple0006 > 0 ~ ple0006,     # Valid values
      ple0006 <= 0 ~ NA_real_,   # Ensure all non-positive values are set to NA
      TRUE ~ NA_real_            # Other invalid values to NA
    )
  ) %>%
  group_by(pid) %>%
  mutate(
    # Impute missing `height` using the first non-NA value within the same `pid`
    height = if_else(
      is.na(height),
      last(na.omit(height), default = NA_real_),  # Use the latest valid value or keep NA if none exist
      height
    )
  ) %>%
  ungroup() %>%
  drop_na(height)  # Drop rows where `height` remains NA

main <- main %>%
  mutate(
    # Rename and handle outliers
    weight = case_when(
      ple0007 > 0 ~ ple0007,     # Valid values
      TRUE ~ NA_real_            # Other invalid values to NA
    )
  ) %>%
  group_by(pid) %>%
  mutate(
    # Impute missing `weight` using average of previous and next years if both are non-NA
    weight = if_else(
      is.na(weight) & !is.na(lag(weight, order_by = syear)) & !is.na(lead(weight, order_by = syear)),
      (lag(weight, order_by = syear) + lead(weight, order_by = syear)) / 2,
      weight
    )
  ) %>%
  ungroup() %>%
  filter(!is.na(weight)) %>%  # Drop rows where `weight` remains NA
  select(-ple0007)  # Drop the original `ple0007` column

#Create BMI using height and weight and BMI categories 
main <- main %>%
  mutate(
    BMI = weight / ((height / 100) ^ 2)  # Convert height to meters and calculate BMI
  )

# Create BMI categorical variable
main <- main %>%
  mutate(
    bmi_categorical = case_when(
      BMI < 18.5 ~ "Underweight",
      BMI >= 18.5 & BMI < 25 ~ "Normal weight",
      BMI >= 25 & BMI < 30 ~ "Overweight",
      BMI >= 30 ~ "Obese",
      TRUE ~ NA_character_  # Catch any unexpected cases
    )
  ) %>%
  mutate(
    bmi_categorical = factor(
      bmi_categorical,
      levels = c("Underweight", "Normal weight", "Overweight", "Obese")
    )
  )
#Visusalisation: Histogram
ggplot(main, aes(x = BMI)) +
  geom_histogram(binwidth = 1, fill = "purple", color = "black", alpha = 0.7) +
  labs(
    title = "Distribution of BMI",
    x = "BMI",
    y = "Count"

3.2.3 Smoking and Number of Cigarettes

# Create `smoking_dummy`
main <- main %>%
  arrange(pid, syear) %>%  # Ensure data is ordered by pid and syear
  group_by(pid) %>%
  mutate(
    # Impute -5 or -8 using dynamic lag and lead
    ple0081_h = ifelse(ple0081_h %in% c(-5, -8), NA_real_, ple0081_h),
    ple0081_h = {
      temp <- ple0081_h
      for (i in seq_len(n())) {
        if (is.na(temp[i])) {
          # Check lag and lead values iteratively
          lag_idx <- which(!is.na(temp) & row_number() < i)
          lead_idx <- which(!is.na(temp) & row_number() > i)

          if (length(lag_idx) > 0 && length(lead_idx) > 0) {
            nearest <- ifelse(
              (i - lag_idx[length(lag_idx)]) <= (lead_idx[1] - i),
              lag_idx[length(lag_idx)],
              lead_idx[1]
            )
          } else if (length(lag_idx) > 0) {
            nearest <- lag_idx[length(lag_idx)]
          } else if (length(lead_idx) > 0) {
            nearest <- lead_idx[1]
          } else {
            nearest <- NA
          }

          if (!is.na(nearest)) {
            temp[i] <- temp[nearest]
          }
        }
      }
      temp
    }
  ) %>%
  ungroup() %>%
  # Transform ple0081_h
  mutate(
    ple0081_h = case_when(
      ple0081_h == -2 ~ 2,  # Treat -2 as "no" (2)
      ple0081_h > 0 ~ ple0081_h,  # Keep valid values (1 = yes, 2 = no)
      TRUE ~ NA_real_  # Set all other cases to NA
    )
  ) %>%
  filter(!is.na(ple0081_h)) %>%  # Drop rows where ple0081_h remains NA
  # Create smoking_dummy
  mutate(smoking_dummy = if_else(ple0081_h == 1, 1, 0))  # 1 for yes, 0 for no

# Creating number of cigarettes
main <- main %>%
  arrange(pid, syear) %>%  # Ensure data is ordered by pid and syear
  group_by(pid) %>%
  mutate(
    # Impute -5 or -8 using dynamic lag and lead
    ple0086_v4 = ifelse(ple0086_v4 %in% c(-5, -8), NA_real_, ple0086_v4),
    ple0086_v4 = {
      temp <- ple0086_v4
      for (i in seq_len(n())) {
        if (is.na(temp[i])) {
          lag_idx <- which(!is.na(temp) & row_number() < i)
          lead_idx <- which(!is.na(temp) & row_number() > i)

          if (length(lag_idx) > 0 && length(lead_idx) > 0) {
            nearest <- ifelse(
              (i - lag_idx[length(lag_idx)]) <= (lead_idx[1] - i),
              lag_idx[length(lag_idx)],
              lead_idx[1]
            )
          } else if (length(lag_idx) > 0) {
            nearest <- lag_idx[length(lag_idx)]
          } else if (length(lead_idx) > 0) {
            nearest <- lead_idx[1]
          } else {
            nearest <- NA
          }

          if (!is.na(nearest)) {
            temp[i] <- temp[nearest]
          }
        }
      }
      temp
    }
  ) %>%

      TRUE ~ NA_real_  # Set invalid values to NA
    )
  ) %>%
  filter(!is.na(ple0086_v4)) %>%  # Drop rows where ple0086_v4 remains NA
  # Create nb_of_cigarettes

4.2 Tenure and Employment Status

# Transform tenure (pgerwzeit) and employment status (pgemplst)
main <- main %>%
  arrange(pid, syear) %>%  # Ensure data is ordered by pid and syear
  group_by(pid) %>%
  mutate(
    # Impute -5 or -8 for `pgerwzeit` using dynamic lag and lead
    tenure = ifelse(pgerwzeit %in% c(-5, -8), NA_real_, pgerwzeit),
    tenure = {
      temp <- tenure
      for (i in seq_len(n())) {
        if (is.na(temp[i])) {
          # Check lag and lead values iteratively
          lag_idx <- which(!is.na(temp) & row_number() < i)
          lead_idx <- which(!is.na(temp) & row_number() > i)
          
          if (length(lag_idx) > 0 && length(lead_idx) > 0) {
            # Choose the closest valid value
            nearest <- ifelse(
              (i - lag_idx[length(lag_idx)]) <= (lead_idx[1] - i),
              lag_idx[length(lag_idx)],
              lead_idx[1]
            )
          } else if (length(lag_idx) > 0) {
            nearest <- lag_idx[length(lag_idx)]
          } else if (length(lead_idx) > 0) {
            nearest <- lead_idx[1]
          } else {
            nearest <- NA
          }
          
          if (!is.na(nearest)) {
            temp[i] <- temp[nearest]
          }
        }
      }
      temp
    },
    # Set `-2` to 0
    tenure = ifelse(is.na(tenure) & pgerwzeit == -2, 0, tenure)
  ) %>%
  ungroup() %>%  # Ungroup after grouped operations
  mutate(
    tenure = ifelse(tenure < 0, NA_real_, tenure)  # Ensure no negative tenure remains
  ) %>%  
  mutate(
    employment_status_categorical = case_when(
      pgemplst == -2 ~ 5,
      pgemplst == 1 ~ 1,
      pgemplst == 2 ~ 2,
      pgemplst == 3 ~ 3,
      pgemplst == 4 ~ 4,
      pgemplst == 5 ~ 5,
      pgemplst == 6 ~ 6,
      TRUE ~ NA_real_
    ),
    employed_dummy = ifelse(employment_status_categorical %in% c(1, 2), 1, 0)
  ) %>%
  drop_na(employment_status_categorical) %>%  # Remove rows with invalid values
  drop_na(tenure) %>%  # Remove rows with NA values in tenure
  mutate(
    employment_status_categorical = factor(
      employment_status_categorical,
      levels = 1:6,
      labels = c(
        "Full-time", 
        "Part-time", 
        "Vocational training", 
        "Irregular part-time", 
        "Unemployed", 
        "Sheltered workshop"
      )
    )
  ) %>%
  select(-pgemplst)  # Drop the original `pgemplst` column

#Visualisation: Bar Plots
ggplot(main, aes(x = employment_status_categorical)) +
  geom_bar(fill = "steelblue", color = "black") +
  labs(
    title = "Distribution of Employment Status",
    x = "Employment Status",
    y = "Count"
  ) +
  theme_minimal()

# Handle `net_income` transformation

    net_income = ifelse(pglabnet %in% c(-5, -8), NA_real_, pglabnet),  # Replace -5 and -8 with NA
    # Iterative imputation using lag and lead
    net_income = {
      temp <- net_income
      for (i in seq_len(n())) {
        if (is.na(temp[i])) {
          # Check lag and lead values iteratively
          lag_idx <- which(!is.na(temp) & row_number() < i)
          lead_idx <- which(!is.na(temp) & row_number() > i)
          
          if (length(lag_idx) > 0 && length(lead_idx) > 0) {
            # Choose the closest valid value

              (i - lag_idx[length(lag_idx)]) <= (lead_idx[1] - i),
              lag_idx[length(lag_idx)],
              lead_idx[1]
            )

4.4 Unemployment

# Transform total years unemployed (pgexpue)
main <- main %>%
  arrange(pid, syear) %>%  # Ensure data is ordered by pid and syear
  group_by(pid) %>%
  mutate(
    # Replace -5 and -8 with NA for imputation
    total_years_unemployment = ifelse(pgexpue %in% c(-5, -8), NA_real_, pgexpue),
    # Iterative imputation with adjustment for year differences
    total_years_unemployment = {
      temp <- total_years_unemployment
      for (i in seq_len(n())) {
        if (is.na(temp[i])) {
          # Find the nearest valid value in lag or lead
          lag_idx <- which(!is.na(temp) & row_number() < i)
          lead_idx <- which(!is.na(temp) & row_number() > i)
          
          if (length(lag_idx) > 0 && length(lead_idx) > 0) {
            # Choose the closer value between lag and lead
            nearest <- ifelse(
              (i - lag_idx[length(lag_idx)]) <= (lead_idx[1] - i),
              lag_idx[length(lag_idx)],
              lead_idx[1]
            )
          } else if (length(lag_idx) > 0) {
            nearest <- lag_idx[length(lag_idx)]
          } else if (length(lead_idx) > 0) {
            nearest <- lead_idx[1]
          } else {
            nearest <- NA
          }
          
          if (!is.na(nearest)) {
            # Adjust for the difference in years
            year_diff <- syear[i] - syear[nearest]
            temp[i] <- temp[nearest] - year_diff
          }
        }
      }
      temp
    },
    # Transform -2 into 0 after imputation
    total_years_unemployment = ifelse(total_years_unemployment == -2, 0, total_years_unemployment)
  ) %>%
  ungroup() %>%
  # Drop rows where the value remains NA after imputation
  drop_na(total_years_unemployment) %>%
  # Remove the original `pgexpue` column
  select(-pgexpue)
#Visualisation: Bar Plot
ggplot(main, aes(x = total_years_unemployment)) +
  geom_bar(fill = "purple", color = "black") +
  labs(
    title = "Distribution of Total Years Unemployed",
    x = "Total Years Unemployed",
    y = "Count"
  ) +
  theme_minimal()

4.9 Age: Filtering for age between 25 and 55

# Create age and filter age range
main <- main %>%
  arrange(pid, syear) %>%  # Ensure data is sorted by pid and syear
  group_by(pid) %>%
  mutate(
    # Impute `ple0010_h` using the closest valid value in the same group
    ple0010_h = if_else(
      is.na(ple0010_h),
      ple0010_h[!is.na(ple0010_h)] + (syear - syear[!is.na(ple0010_h)]),  # Calculate from closest year
      ple0010_h
    )
  ) %>%
  ungroup() %>%
  mutate(
    age = syear - ple0010_h  # Calculate age based on imputed or existing `ple0010_h`
  ) %>%
  filter(!is.na(ple0010_h) & ple0010_h > 0) %>%  # Filter out invalid entries
  filter(age >= 25 & age <= 55) %>%  # Keep only rows within the age range
  select(-ple0010_h)  # Drop `ple0010_h` after processing

# Visualisation: Histogram
